main event: A professor observed an unidentified flying object in mid-December 195[obscured] in northern Arizona.
interesting points: The object was reported to fly at a speed of 600 mph,The object left a thick, heavy white trail rather than a typical vapor trail,The altitude of the object was estimated between 20,000 to 50,000 feet,The observation occurred early in the morning under clear weather conditions,There are no photographs or sketches included with the report.
witness description: a professor from the University of Colorado, Boulder
